item.title: The Team
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Our team is a group of expert designers, engineers, builders and real estate professionals. Our principals are highly experienced in design and build projects, holding licenses in multiple facets across the industry

Soheil Nakhshab, LEED AP, BPI

Principal, CEO, Co-Founder

Soheil has over 14 years experience in the building industry. His formal education is in structural engineering and he also has hands on experience in the field working on and managing countless construction projects. Soheil is responsible for overseeing all engineering, construction, design-build, LEED and business segments of NDD. Soheil's architecture training has come into fruition through rigorous work experience and a natural eye for design. Having a technical education background with architectural talent has allowed Soheil to excel in overseeing the design and build process. His interest in the classical master-builder philosophy has fueled success in combining the architectural process as well as the engineering and constructions of projects as developer.
  • B.S. Civil Engineering, SDSU
  • EIT – 127993
  • General Contractor A & B - #926557
  • LEED AP
  • BPI, Building Analyst Professional
  • BPI, Building Envelope Professional
  • Building Performance Contractor with Energystar
  • HERS Certified
  • AIA, Allied Member
  • SEAOSD, Member
  • SEAOC, Member

Sasan Nakhshab, P.E.

Principal, Co-Founder

Sasan personally oversees all engineering and development projects within the company. He has vast experience in the design and construction industry, including extensive knowledge of the comprehensive application of building codes. He is well versed in a wide range of project types and has developed a sincere level of sensitivity to design issues and the importance of code compliance.
  • B.S. Civil Engineering – CSU Los Angeles
  • M.S. Structural Engineering – USC
  • Registered Professional Engineer - C44563

Nima Nakhshab, CM

Principal, Construction Manager, Co-Founder

Nima currently serves as the construction manager for NDD. He is experienced in many facets of construction for both commercial and residential projects. Nima's responsibilities include oversight of construction projects, along with public relations and marketing.
  • B.A. Business Management, San Marcos State
  • General Contractor A & B – 926557
  • HERS Certified

Mitra Bagheri

Principal, Interior Designer, Co-Founder

Mitra is the lead interior designer at NDD. She specializes in both residential and commercial interiors and works with clients to achieve their specific design goals by guiding them through the material, finish, fixture and furniture selection process. She also handles specifications, purchasing and installation coordination.

Susana Mora

Real Estate Manager

Susana leads the business operations for NDD including day-to-day operations, accounting, business development, marketing and sales. She also specializes in the San Diego real estate market and uses her expertise to assist NDD clients with all their real estate needs.
  • B.S. Communications, SJSU
  • DRE License - #01444176

Georgia Fokas, LEED GA

Project Manager

Georgia brings NDD a background in Architecture with an emphasis in sustainable design. She is well versed in all aspects of LEED. Georgia provides detailed organization skills for all NDD projects ranging from construction documents through LEED certification documentation. Georgia has over 10 years of experience in this industry working on a wide range of projects which include commercial, institutional, government, and residential.
  • B.A. Architecture, New School of Architecture

James Goldbach, HERS

Architecture, Green Project Manager

James brings NDD a background in Architecture, Interior Design, and Construction. Along with these items he is also a Certified Building Auditor specializing in reducing Energy consumption by prescribing cost effective measures for each project. James have over 12 years of experience in the building industry working on commercial, institutional, gov- ernment, and residential projects.
  • HERS Certified, Home Energy Rating System

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Company

Founded in 2003, Nakhshab Development & Design, Inc. (NDD) is an internationally renowned design-build firm with headquarters in San Diego, California. NDD is committed to designing and building projects that create the greatest value for the end users as well as the community at large. It is the goal at NDD to make the experience of the built environment integrated with the natural world as positive as possible. Projects last a lifetime and have a vital role in the way people feel and interact with their environment and in communities; we believe it is our duty to develop our neighborhoods to fulfill the demands of residents to grow and develop while also being mindful of the future. Our projects affect the way people feel and interact with their environment.  They also have an impact on the surrounding community. Our designs are always mindful of the future and customized to the unique needs of each of our clients. Drawing inspiration from the quintessential convention of the “master-builder” in which building design, engineering, and construction were overseen by a single party, NDD values this tradition with a horizontal approach and expertise across the industry when it comes to the realization of a project. From the initial aesthetic design and conception, to engineering, and ultimately construction, NDD has the capacity to truly and fully design and build projects in the comprehensive nature of the master-builder philosophy. While executing the traditional aspects of project construction, the NDD team also implements sustainable methods into building whether or not LEED certification is an objective. This complete integration allows us to build projects more efficiently and seamlessly while also constructing sustainably and reducing the cost of building. NDD development is focused on enriching the experience of users both within our projects as well as the greater community. We value building projects of refined and unique character that leave a lasting positive impression. Our designers accentuate site characteristics and take advantage of positive attributes while designing for improvements that will minimize undesirable property features. At our core, NDD is a team of expert designers, engineers and builders committed to providing our clients with comprehensive services while adding value to our community.

Mission

To comprehensively design and build projects which significantly enhance the quality of life and encourage a unique experience for intended users as well as positively affecting the greater community.

Values

Community

At NDD it is our belief that when a community flourishes, individuals benefit as well. We strive to have a positive effect on and improve the neighborhoods in which we develop; both fostering and helping to create a quality sense of place.

Ingenuity

Due to our extensive background and experience in the industry, NDD is to creatively innovate during the design + build process and create projects that incorporate the newest design and construction methods. The NDD team has a track record of taking difficult sites and realizing elegant and functional projects.

Distinction

Our projects stand out from others because we believe that craftsmanship comes first. We benefit from our boutique business model by delivering the most cost-effective, quality product possible without sacrificing the project vision.

Character

The NDD family is committed to a culture of accountability and this value runs deep in our business practices. Clients can expect complete transparency. Every project we build has the quality and attention to detail that our designers would appreciate for their own space. In other word, we treat our clients like family and handle all of our projects as if they are being built for ourselves.

Experience

NDD has over 30 years of industry experience on staff, including numerous award-winning projects.

Reputation

NDD has been published in notable publications including but not limited to: Dwell Magazine, Rivera Magazine, Luxe Magazine, San Diego Home & Garden, Ranch & Coast, Union Tribune, and Presidio Sentinel

item.title: Services
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Services Overview

Nakhshab Development & Design, Inc. (NDD) provides a comprehensive collection of services including complete design + build, building design, structural engineering, construction, sustainability, and LEED services to a range of clients including residential, multi-family, and commercial.

Background

NDD structural engineering services are the cornerstone of our business and span across all segments of the market. NDD is active in development, construction and design + build in residential, multi-family and commercial markets.

Depth

Our in-house expertise with a wide range of practices including building design, engineering, building code, sustainability, and construction are what set our firm apart.  We have integrated our extensive knowledge centers to create a more cohesive and efficient design + build process.

Detail

Our boutique business model allows us to focus on our clients. We encourage the development of close personal relationships with each of our clients and work “in the trenches” to create the most value for you. As engineers, designers and builders, we understand the importance of designing and constructing a project with the shortest timeline and at the lowest possible cost.

item.title: Design Services
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Nakhshab Development & Design (NDD) offers a full range of design services. Our talented designers can develop a complete building design package from initial concept, to design development, through to the completion of construction documents. Whether a project is new construction or a remodel of an existing structure, our team provides the creativity and design know-how to develop designs that exceed clients expectations.

Building Design

All of the aesthetic and functional elements of a project are handled by the NDD team. Construction documents for submittal to the appropriate governing body for approval are provided as well as the design of new structures, a minor remodel or small addition, and also devising plans for a total overhaul of an existing structure.

Interior Design

Our designers provide a complete interior design concept with this service. This includes the selection of fixtures, finishes, materials and furnishings for a project. NDD takes care of purchasing and hiring sub-contractors to ensure seamless installation.

Landscape Architecture

This service goes hand in hand with our design service. NDD works with local landscape architects that provide concepts and detailed landscape design drawings to a client.

Title 24

NDD provides this service at no additional cost to our clients on all design projects as part of the construction documents we produce.

Code Consulting

Non-Structural code design includes plans and plan review and design for fire safety, exiting issues, and accessibility requirements. NDD reviews all codes relative to the aesthetic design of a building. Our extensive experience with government and regulatory agency's procedures enables us to eliminate any potential issues with these requirements. NDD provides this service at no cost to our clients on each structural engineering project.

item.title: Engineering Services
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Nakhshab Development & Design offers a full range of structural design, review, and consulting services. Whether you're an architect, developer, or owner we can provide specialized structural engineering services for both new construction and renovation/modernization projects. It is our mission to create value for each one of our clients through value engineering, lower construction costs and a shorter design phase. Our combination of engineering, building code, and construction knowledge allows our team to foresee problems before a project begins. Our areas of expertise include residential, multi-family, mixed use, commercial, institutional, and government projects.

Structural Engineering

NDD designs all of the structural systems for a project. NDD provides construction documents for submittal to the appropriate governing body for approval. If designing for an existing building we will complete a feasibility study prior to design.

Seismic Retrofit

This service includes a review of the current structural conditions of a building and recommendations/options for design and construction. This service includes inspection, written or verbal assessment, and recommendations for client. We then provide construction documents for submittal to the appropriate governing body.

Fire & Life Safety

Non-Structural code design includes plan review and design for fire safety, exiting issues, and accessibility requirements. We review all codes relative to the architectural design of a building. Our extensive experience with government and regulatory agency's procedures enables us to eliminate any issues with these requirements. We provide this service at no cost to our clients on each structural engineering project.

item.title: Construction Services
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Nakhshab Development & Design is a full service general contracting company with both contractors A & B licenses. We are experienced and accomplished builders of commercial tenant improvements, multi-family, and high-end custom residences. What sets us apart from other general contractors is the fact that our staff is also made up of licensed professional engineers with over 30 years of experience in the industry.

Construction Engineering

This service includes planning and management of a project from start to finish. We engage in quality assurance and quality control, building and site layout surveys, onsite material testing, cost estimating, planning and scheduling, safety engineering, materials procurement, and cost engineering and budgeting.

Construction Management

NDD provides planning, coordination, and control of a project from concept to completion. NDD aims to exceed our client's requirements in order to produce a functionally and financially viable project that will be completed on time, within authorized cost, and to the highest of quality standards.

Project Management

NDD oversees the planning and organization of a project as well as the securing and managing of resources to bring about the successful completion of specific project goals and objectives.

Cost Estimating

NDD provides full pre-construction services, which include cost estimating projects from concept to construction document phases. As designers and builders, NDD has the ability to ensure accurate and viable cost models for our clients to minimize change orders. Whether negotiated or bid, NDD fosters the best sub-contractor relationships to guarantee the most competitive prices combined with quality craftsmanship.

Value Engineering (VE)

Value Engineering is the systematic analysis and exploration of alternative options to stay on budget and save on building costs. Thus, the ultimate objective of VE is to preserve the look and function of the project, while finding alternatives to lower the overall cost. Value Engineering also aims to increase the functional life of a project by evaluating initial costs, life-cycle costs, financing costs, maintenance costs, and ownership costs.

Constructability Review

In order to optimize field administration and minimize change orders, NDD will continually provide constructability reviews on our designs. We strive for completeness, accuracy, and system compatibility. These reviews result in shorter schedules, more precise cost forecasts, and client satisfaction.

This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Montreal, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Sustainability Services
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[column size='2/3'] Nakhshab Development & Design (NDD) is dedicated to implementing sustainable building and design practices into our work whenever possible. We continue to lead the industry when it comes to green building systems and have successfully completed numerous LEED certified projects. NDD strives to be thoroughly educated on the most up-to-date systems, products and building practices. [/column] [column size='1/3' position='last'] [/column]

LEED Project Management

NDD is a sustainability oriented company and we take our construction management service one step further by having the expertise in building a "green" project and possibly obtaining a LEED certification. NDD provides all of the necessary documentation and submittals to the LEED organization and can also take care of submissions for various government-sponsored rebates.

Energy Efficiency & Renewable Energy

NDD provides recommendations on the best systems to use in order to build the most energy efficient project possible, saving the client money and protecting our precious resources. Often, this means incorporating renewable energy systems into a project including the use of solar power, wind power, geothermal power and rain-water harvesting.

Green Material Selection

NDD's designers are well versed in the most up-to-date green products on the market. NDD knows which green products are best suited for each kind of application and can develop a design concept that integrates sustainable materials without sacrificing the aesthetic of a project.

Solar Installation

Solar Installation is the most popular "green" service, NDD can specify and install the most efficient solar system based on the particular project. Solar power can be used to generate electricity and heat water, which greatly increases the efficiency of a project and substantially reduces energy costs.

If you manage to score one, though, you might get stuck with a lot of expensive renovations. Not so in Mission Hills, where mid-century style and modern convenience go hand-in-hand at Nakhshab Design & Development’s recently unveiled Revival properties. Read More

item.title: Homer Delawie Revived
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Nakhshab Development & Design has teamed up with Magnus Architects to restore a Mission Hills home built in 1965 by iconic mid-century modern architect Homer Delawie. Not only did they renovate and update the dwelling while preserving its original architectural design concepts and characteristics, they also incorporated those concepts into two new single-family homes—each 4,400 square feet—built alongside the Delawie residence. The trio of homes is a stunning display of midcentury design revived for 21st-century living. Read More

item.title: Design + Build
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Design Philosophy

We start with the property and design from there. All of the aesthetic and functional elements of a project are handled by the NDD team. Each and every project site is treated with due diligence and the site-specific conditions are given close attention. At NDD, every project is a unique opportunity to improve not only the function and value of a site, but to create a timeless impression. We spend a significant amount of time on the location in order to capture and consider any and every possible detail that will improve the final project. To achieve sustainability, passive design methods are implemented into all of our projects.  We believe that sustainable practices should be a part of building design regardless of LEED goals.

Design + Build Benefit

Our expertise in design, engineering, and construction enables our clients to benefit from the cohesiveness of the finished product as well as improved cost efficiencies through our uniquely integrated system. By working with our clients from start to finish on their projects, we streamline the design + build process and remove much of the confusion and hassle of traditional construction. All aspects of our clients’ projects are managed in-house and built to quality standards through our comprehensive process. Our goal is to surpass our clients’ expectations and build projects that enhance the site they reside on as well as the surrounding neighborhood. NDD's talented designers have the ability develop a complete building design package from initial concept, to design development, through to the completion of construction documents.

Innovative Building Methods

Our structural engineering roots enable us to uniquely approach challenging building sites with innovative methods. NDD is a licensed full service general contracting company with both contractors A & B licenses. We are experienced and accomplished builders of commercial spaces, multi-family buildings, and high-end custom residences. What sets us apart from other general contractors is the fact that our staff is also made up of designers and licensed professional engineers with over 30 years of experience in the industry.

Whether a property has an extreme steep hillside or is a perceived unbuildable canyon lot, NDD has been able to creatively address the issues and design stunning, award-winning projects. Our team provides the creativity and design know-how to develop designs that exceed clients' expectations.

Streamlined Process

We provide true and complete Design + Build projects as we manage the complete project, other aspects NDD provides competency include:

⁘ Interior Design

⁘ Landscape Architecture

⁘ Title 24

⁘ Code Consulting

⁘ Construction Engineering

⁘ Project Management

item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: If you travel around Mission Hills you will quickly realize that the community is quite diverse, in terms of architecture, style, history and tastes. Because of the interests, attitudes and backgrounds of the residents, it’s easy to understand the reason for this diversity. Mission Hills’ residents seek to identify themselves by the homes they live in. Read More

item.title: Modern Multi-Generational Green Living
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: I know, I know, another green home in California. Seems like half the releases we get lately are about some Californian completing a sustainable home. Well, this one just so happens to be the first LEED Gold home in San Diego. If that’s not special enough for you, check out the age range of the people living there 2 to 64. Long ago, I read somewhere the American family was fairly unique in the sense that it almost never included extended family. It was almost always exclusively the nuclear family. Well, times must be a changin’ because while it seems for us that we’ve been doing a lot of sustainable homes in California, I have noticed that most of the sustainable homes we’ve covered have had a senior suite of some kind. Have any studies ever been done about how much a nuclear family consumes versus an extended family? I mean, it seems like it would make sense that people would consume less if grandpa and grandma were living with them, but I could be wrong. Read More

The two-story home incorporates natural ventilation, high-efficiency building materials, xeriscape landscaping and a solar energy system. The home is certified as LEED for Home Gold. Read More

item.title: Sofia Lofts
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Design, Engineering + Build

With the construction of the Sofia Lofts, Nakhshab Development & Design introduces historic Golden Hill to a sharply new wave mid-century modern, distinctively community- oriented approach to urban living. Appealing Mid-Century Modern design and forward-looking sustainability features (including on-site electric vehicle chargers and an innovative bike-sharing program) underline how Sofia Lofts deliberately creates an environment meant to foster both multi-generational living and an “age in place” concept intended to allow residents to move to larger and smaller units with a range of amenities over the decades, as their needs require. A total of 16 studio, one and two-bedroom rentals have been constructed around an existing, historic three- bedroom home. The “community within a community” objective is achieved by a layout in which all units surround an intimate common area with a BBQ grill, a lounge area, a space for showing movies outdoors and other shared activities. The idea is for all residents to mingle and interact, very much like a large family of several generations. The “age in place” concept is served by attracting young residents with inexpensive studios, and older residents with larger units, of which five are two stories. At Sofia Lofts, everyone who values Golden Hill's setting as a quiet neighborhood that enjoys close, ultra- convenient proximity to San Diego's stellar educational, cultural attractions never will need to leave. The unit amenities and development highlights, as is true of all Nakhshab Development & Design projects, are community-oriented and as environmentally progressive as current technology allows. Earning LEED Platinum certification, Sofia Lofts combine a Mid-Century Modern aesthetic and a generous helping of historic charm to create a micro- community that both reflects and enhances the surrounding neighborhood. Solar PV will off-set electricity usage, and the many “green,” passive design elements include high-density floors, floor-to-ceiling glass that floods units with natural light and windows placed for optimum natural ventilation. High-efficiency Energy Star appliances, low-usage lighting and low-flow water designs are integral to Sofia Lofts' careful design. The expansive balconies and patios will allow residents to enjoy the breezy, shady and very hip Golden Hill setting even more.

Community

⁘ Minutes away from Downtown, Balboa Park, South Park, and so much more ⁘ Walkable community with easy access to public transportation and freeways ⁘ Weekly Farmer's Market, quaint local businesses and beautiful tree lined streets

Modern Lifestyle

⁘ Open concept designs with modern features and amenities ⁘ Floor-to-ceiling windows offering bright and airy spaces ⁘ Historic character blended with contemporary designs ⁘ Patios, balconies and communal areas ⁘ Gated community for added privacy ⁘ Wi-Fi included

Sustainability

⁘ LEED Platinum design specifications ⁘ Solar photovoltaic system for lower electric bills ⁘ Energy Star appliances ⁘ Onsite Bike Sharing ⁘ Electric vehicle charging stations ⁘ Onsite Car2Go

Studio, 2, and 3 Bedrooms Available

If interested, please send us an email:

SofiaLofts@NDDinc.net

www.SofiaLofts.com
